 splits it into child beads) is writing the parent&#39;s ID as a dep edge on every child. This produces an unbreakable deadlock:&#xA;&#xA;  e29892a4 (parent, open) -- parent --&gt; child_A&#xA;  e29892a4 -- parent --&gt; child_B&#xA;  child_A.deps = [e29892a4]           &lt;- BAD: parent is also a dep&#xA;  child_B.deps = [child_A, e29892a4]  &lt;- BAD&#xA;&#xA;The parent stays open until its children close. Every child is blocked on the parent. Nothing can be claimed. ddx work loops on the parent, the orchestrator emits &#39;mixed_commit_and_no_changes_rationale&#39;, the worker retries, and burns claim budget without progress.&#xA;&#xA;Observed scenario (niflheim, 2026-06-04 04:30-05:13 UTC):&#xA;- Parent: niflheim-e29892a4 (&#39;feat(delta): async write-behind ...&#39;)&#xA;- 10 children created during planning loops (23223661, a44a8ceb, 054c89b7, 0470ba0d, f10e9e35, f076b08c, 6c041162, 94e1df73, 9da62c2d, 5e4f9fb2)&#xA;- Every child carried deps=[..siblings.., niflheim-e29892a4]&#xA;- ~50 minutes of agent time + 4 strong-policy claude/opus attempts with zero feature commits; only tracker chores&#xA;- Unwedged manually by closing the parent via &#39;ddx bead close&#39;, after which siblings drained correctly in foundational order&#xA;&#xA;Root cause is structural, not model-capability — auto-upgrading to a stronger model does NOT fix this. The orchestrator already detects the no-progress state but its only remediation is &#39;retry parent&#39;, which re-enters the same loop.&#xA;&#xA;There is also a &#39;project root mutation rejected (continuing)&#39; warning emitted by the readiness check during this state; that&#39;s a downstream symptom of the same problem, not the cause.&#xA;&#xA;PROPOSED FIX&#xA;Implement only this child acceptance slice:&#xA;- &#39;ddx bead dep add &lt;bead&gt; &lt;dep&gt;&#39; HARD-REJECTS the edge when &lt;dep&gt; is &lt;bead&gt;&#39;s parent OR any ancestor in the parent chain. Error message names the offending ancestor and prints the relevant parent-chain. Test: ddx_bead_dep_add_rejects_parent_ancestor.&#xA;- &#39;ddx bead create --depends-on X --parent Y&#39; with X == Y (or X an ancestor of Y) HARD-REJECTS at creation time with the same error shape as AC #1. No silent rewrite.&#xA;&#xA;NON-SCOPE&#xA;Do not implement parent acceptance criteria assigned to sibling child beads. Preserve every parent non-scope constraint unless this child explicitly narrows it.     </description>     <acceptance> 1. &#39;ddx bead dep add &lt;bead&gt; &lt;dep&gt;&#39; HARD-REJECTS the edge when &lt;dep&gt; is &lt;bead&gt;&#39;s parent OR any ancestor in the parent chain. Error message names the offending ancestor and prints the relevant parent-chain. Test: ddx_bead_dep_add_rejects_parent_ancestor.&#xA;2. &#39;ddx bead create --depends-on X --parent Y&#39; with X == Y (or X an ancestor of Y) HARD-REJECTS at creation time with the same error shape as AC #1. No silent rewrite.&#xA;3. cd cli &amp;&amp; go test ./... passes.&#xA;4. lefthook run pre-commit passes.     </acceptance>     <labels>area:tracker, area:lifecycle, area:decomposition, kind:safety, kind:correctness, ac-quality:needs-refinement, decomposed</labels>     <metadata parent="ddx-e19185aa" base-rev="d56d48c6e216e98ddf2707215f0df5a6f1f3a98a" bundle=".ddx/executions/20260607T033207-f897f09d"/>   </bead>   <governing>     <note>No governing references were pre-resolved. The bead description above is the primary contract. If it names files, specs, or prior beads, read them first. Ground decisions in repository state; do not guess.</note>   </governing> </execute-bead> 
