rentAncestorDependency.&#xA;&#xA;3. Existing valid dependency graphs, including `parent -&gt; child` edges used to hold decomposed parents until children close, still pass and remain claimable according to existing queue rules. Test: TestDepAddAllowsParentDependingOnChild.&#xA;&#xA;4. Verification gate passes: `cd cli &amp;&amp; go test ./cmd/... ./internal/bead/... -run &#39;TestDepAddRejectsParentAncestor|TestBeadCreateRejectsParentAncestorDependency|TestDepAddAllowsParentDependingOnChild&#39; -count=1`.&#xA;&#xA;5. Repository gate passes: `lefthook run pre-commit`.     </acceptance>     <labels>area:tracker, area:lifecycle, area:decomposition, kind:safety, kind:correctness, ac-quality:needs-refinement</labels>     <metadata parent="ddx-e19185aa" base-rev="c9aadb0c061b757731633ca449192b0c92897fa2" bundle=".ddx/executions/20260607T031431-779d771a"/>   </bead>   <governing>     <note>No governing references were pre-resolved. The bead description above is the primary contract. If it names files, specs, or prior beads, read them first. Ground decisions in repository state; do not guess.</note>   </governing> </execute-bead> 
